<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> The 1850-11-02 Punch issue is credited with bestowing the "Crystal Palace" name on the design by <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFStrieter1999">Strieter, Terry (1999). <i>Nineteenth-Century European Art: A Topical Dictionary</i>. p.&#160;50. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/031329898X" class="internal">ISBN 031329898X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Nineteenth-Century+European+Art%3A+A+Topical+Dictionary&amp;rft.aulast=Strieter&amp;rft.aufirst=Terry&amp;rft.au=Strieter%2C+Terry&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B50&amp;rft.isbn=031329898X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (And <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/london/content/articles/2004/08/10/cp_dinosaur_feature.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.bbc.co.uk/london/content/articles/2004/08/10/cp_dinosaur_feature.shtml" rel="nofollow">"Crystal Palace"</a>. BBC<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/london/content/articles/2004/08/10/cp_dinosaur_feature.shtml" class="external free" title="http://www.bbc.co.uk/london/content/articles/2004/08/10/cp_dinosaur_feature.shtml" rel="nofollow">http://www.bbc.co.uk/london/content/articles/2004/08/10/cp_dinosaur_feature.shtml</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-11-21</span>.  "The term 'Crystal Palace' was first applied to Paxton's building by Punch in its issue of 2nd November 1850"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Crystal+Palace&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=BBC&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Flondon%2Fcontent%2Farticles%2F2004%2F08%2F10%2Fcp_dinosaur_feature.shtml&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.) Punch had originally sided with <i>The Times</i> against the Exhibition committee's own proposal of a fixed brick structure, but featured the Crystal Palace heavily throughout 1851 (for example in <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.hrionline.ac.uk/luceneweb/hri3/display.jsp?mode=sciper&amp;file=PU1-20.html&amp;reveal=issue_PU1-20-17" class="external text" title="http://www.hrionline.ac.uk/luceneweb/hri3/display.jsp?mode=sciper&amp;file=PU1-20.html&amp;reveal=issue_PU1-20-17" rel="nofollow">"Punch Issue 502"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.hrionline.ac.uk/luceneweb/hri3/display.jsp?mode=sciper&amp;file=PU1-20.html&amp;reveal=issue_PU1-20-17" class="external free" title="http://www.hrionline.ac.uk/luceneweb/hri3/display.jsp?mode=sciper&amp;file=PU1-20.html&amp;reveal=issue_PU1-20-17" rel="nofollow">http://www.hrionline.ac.uk/luceneweb/hri3/display.jsp?mode=sciper&amp;file=PU1-20.html&amp;reveal=issue_PU1-20-17</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Punch+Issue+502&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrionline.ac.uk%2Fluceneweb%2Fhri3%2Fdisplay.jsp%3Fmode%3Dsciper%26file%3DPU1-20.html%26reveal%3Dissue_PU1-20-17&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> included the article "Travels into the Interior of the Crystal Palace" of February 1851). Any earlier name has been lost, according to <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Crystal%20Palace" class="external text" title="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Crystal%20Palace" rel="nofollow">"Everything2 <i>Crystal Palace</i> Exhibition Building Design #251"</a>. 2003<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Crystal%20Palace" class="external free" title="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Crystal%20Palace" rel="nofollow">http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Crystal%20Palace</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Everything2+%27%27Crystal+Palace%27%27+Exhibition+Building+Design+%23251&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Feverything2.com%2Findex.pl%3Fnode%3DCrystal%2520Palace&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHobhouse2002">Hobhouse, Hermione (2002). <i>The Crystal Palace and the Great Exhibition of the Works of Industry of All Nations</i>. p.&#160;34. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0485115751" class="internal">ISBN 0485115751</a>.  "It was essentially a <a href="/wiki/Modular" title="Modular" class="mw-redirect">modular</a> building of iron, wood and glass, built of components which were meant to be recyclable."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Crystal+Palace+and+the+Great+Exhibition+of+the+Works+of+Industry+of+All+Nations&amp;rft.aulast=Hobhouse&amp;rft.aufirst=Hermione&amp;rft.au=Hobhouse%2C+Hermione&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B34&amp;rft.isbn=0485115751&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> The <a href="/wiki/Prefabricated" title="Prefabricated" class="mw-redirect">prefabricated</a> parts were constructed in the manufacture's ironworks and sawmills (page 36).</li>
<li id="cite_note-dukemag-3">^ <a href="#cite_ref-dukemag_3-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-dukemag_3-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-dukemag_3-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-dukemag_3-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.dukemagazine.duke.edu/dukemag/issues/111206/depgal2.html" class="external text" title="http://www.dukemagazine.duke.edu/dukemag/issues/111206/depgal2.html" rel="nofollow">"The Great Exhibition of 1851"</a>. <i>Duke Magazine</i>. 2006-11<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.dukemagazine.duke.edu/dukemag/issues/111206/depgal2.html" class="external free" title="http://www.dukemagazine.duke.edu/dukemag/issues/111206/depgal2.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.dukemagazine.duke.edu/dukemag/issues/111206/depgal2.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-07-30</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+Great+Exhibition+of+1851&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2006-11&amp;rft.pub=%27%27Duke+Magazine%27%27&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dukemagazine.duke.edu%2Fdukemag%2Fissues%2F111206%2Fdepgal2.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> The peak figure of 2,000 workers daily is given in: <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book"><i>The Crystal Palace and the Great Exhibition</i>. p.&#160;34. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0485115751" class="internal">ISBN 0485115751</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Crystal+Palace+and+the+Great+Exhibition&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B34&amp;rft.isbn=0485115751&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> and by the University of Virginia's <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/allcach2k/Programme/session1.html" class="external text" title="http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/allcach2k/Programme/session1.html" rel="nofollow">"Modeling the Crystal Palace"</a>. 2001<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/allcach2k/Programme/session1.html" class="external free" title="http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/allcach2k/Programme/session1.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.arts.gla.ac.uk/allcach2k/Programme/session1.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Modeling+the+Crystal+Palace&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.arts.gla.ac.uk%2Fallcach2k%2FProgramme%2Fsession1.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> project: <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.iath.virginia.edu/london/model/animation.html#" class="external text" title="http://www.iath.virginia.edu/london/model/animation.html#" rel="nofollow">"<i>The Crystal Palace Animation</i> Exterior and Interior"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.iath.virginia.edu/london/model/animation.html#" class="external free" title="http://www.iath.virginia.edu/london/model/animation.html#" rel="nofollow">http://www.iath.virginia.edu/london/model/animation.html#</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-11-20</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=%27%27The+Crystal+Palace+Animation%27%27+Exterior+and+Interior&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iath.virginia.edu%2Flondon%2Fmodel%2Fanimation.html%23&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/history/default.asp?ID=10" class="external text" title="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/history/default.asp?ID=10" rel="nofollow">"Crystal Palace history <i>Leaving Hyde Park</i> October 1851"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/history/default.asp?ID=10" class="external free" title="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/history/default.asp?ID=10" rel="nofollow">http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/history/default.asp?ID=10</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Crystal+Palace+history+%27%27Leaving+Hyde+Park%27%27+October+1851&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk%2Fhistory%2Fdefault.asp%3FID%3D10&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/history/default.asp?ID=11" class="external text" title="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/history/default.asp?ID=11" rel="nofollow">"Crystal Palace history <i>The Building</i> 1852 - 1854"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/history/default.asp?ID=11" class="external free" title="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/history/default.asp?ID=11" rel="nofollow">http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/history/default.asp?ID=11</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-11-21</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Crystal+Palace+history%27%27+The+Building%27%27+1852+-+1854&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk%2Fhistory%2Fdefault.asp%3FID%3D11&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> These amounts are in successive years, and partly reflect the extension to five stories made at Sydenham. The £150,000 cost of the Hyde Park Crystal Palace includes the (re-usable) component material cost, so the extent to which the reconstructed Palace had an (unexpectedly) higher construction cost is even greater than the comparison of totals implies.</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/archives/m/memorial_from_the_national_sun.aspx" class="external text" title="http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/archives/m/memorial_from_the_national_sun.aspx" rel="nofollow">"Memorial from the National Sunday League on the Sunday opening of the British Museum"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/archives/m/memorial_from_the_national_sun.aspx" class="external free" title="http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/archives/m/memorial_from_the_national_sun.aspx" rel="nofollow">http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/archives/m/memorial_from_the_national_sun.aspx</a></span>.  "working men and their families [...] worked long hours and all day Saturday. Many could not afford a day's unpaid leave to come to the Museum."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Memorial+from+the+National+Sunday+League+on+the+Sunday+opening+of+the+British+Museum&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.britishmuseum.org%2Fexplore%2Fhighlights%2Fhighlight_objects%2Farchives%2Fm%2Fmemorial_from_the_national_sun.aspx&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> The Great Exhibition was always closed on Sunday, see: <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.crystal.dircon.co.uk/mrskpg.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.crystal.dircon.co.uk/mrskpg.htm" rel="nofollow">"Crystal Palace - On a hot summer's day <i>Facts and Figures</i>"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.crystal.dircon.co.uk/mrskpg.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.crystal.dircon.co.uk/mrskpg.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.crystal.dircon.co.uk/mrskpg.htm</a></span>.  "No Sunday opening was allowed, no alcohol, no smoking and no dogs"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Crystal+Palace+-+On+a+hot+summer%27s+day+%27%27Facts+and+Figures%27%27&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.crystal.dircon.co.uk%2Fmrskpg.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>. The Crystal Palace at Sydenham continued the observance, opening only to <a href="/wiki/Shareholder" title="Shareholder">shareholders</a> on Sundays: <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/History/default.asp?ID=12" class="external text" title="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/History/default.asp?ID=12" rel="nofollow">"Crystal Palace History <i>Open again</i>"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/History/default.asp?ID=12" class="external free" title="http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/History/default.asp?ID=12" rel="nofollow">http://www.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk/History/default.asp?ID=12</a></span>.  "neither the building nor grounds were open on Sundays"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Crystal+Palace+History+%27%27Open+again%27%27&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.crystalpalacefoundation.org.uk%2FHistory%2Fdefault.asp%3FID%3D12&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Crystal_Palace"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
