<li><a href="http://www.ge35.dial.pipex.com/sirjosephpaxton1.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ge35.dial.pipex.com/sirjosephpaxton1.htm" rel="nofollow">Eddie Richardson's page</a> on Sir Joseph Paxton – includes photographs</li>
<li><a href="http://rhaworth.com/os/coor_g.php?pagename=The_Crystal_Palace&amp;params=TQ3425070750_region:GB_scale:25000" class="external text" title="http://rhaworth.com/os/coor_g.php?pagename=The_Crystal_Palace&amp;params=TQ3425070750_region:GB_scale:25000" rel="nofollow">Map sources for the park and surrounding area</a> including Victorian maps showing the palace</li>
<li><a href="http://www.ric.edu/rpotter/cryspal.html" class="external text" title="http://www.ric.edu/rpotter/cryspal.html" rel="nofollow"></a><a href="/wiki/Russell_Potter" title="Russell Potter">Russell Potter</a>'s Crystal Palace Page, with information on the Baird Television studios</li>
<li><a href="http://en.citizendium.org/wiki/Crystal_Palace" class="external text" title="http://en.citizendium.org/wiki/Crystal_Palace" rel="nofollow">Crystal Palace</a> – at <i>Citizendium</i>; includes images.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.iath.virginia.edu/london/model/" class="external text" title="http://www.iath.virginia.edu/london/model/" rel="nofollow">A 3D computer model of the Crystal Palace with images and animation</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.arthurlloyd.co.uk/CrystalPalace.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.arthurlloyd.co.uk/CrystalPalace.htm" rel="nofollow">History of The Crystal Palace</a></li>
